We write:

(p ∧ q) for (p and q)  
(p ∨ q) for (p or q or both)  
(p → q) for (If p then q)  
¬p for not-p  

∀x for (For everything x),
∃x for (There exists something x).

**First-order logic** is logic using just these symbols.

**Propositional logic** (Aussagenlogik) is first-order logic using only ∧, ∨, →
and ¬, not ∀ or ∃.

