## Combinatory Logic

Combinatory logic is a notation to eliminate the need for quantified variables
in mathematical logic.
A combinator is a higher-order function that uses only function application and
earlier defined combinators to define a result from its arguments.
Another way of eliminating quantified variables is Quine's predicate functor
logic. While the expressive power of combinatory logic typically exceeds that
of first-order logic, the expressive power of predicate functor logic is
identical to that of first order logic

